Diagnosis of Chronic Diseases Based on Patients’ Health Records in IoT Healthcare Using a Recommender System
Description
This project presents a MATLAB-based implementation of a medical decision-support framework designed for the diagnosis and treatment recommendation of chronic diseases using electronic health records collected within Internet of Things (IoT) healthcare environments. The proposed system integrates similarity-driven learning and collaborative recommendation mechanisms to assist clinical interpretation of patient data. The model operates in two sequential stages: disease identification through instance-based classification and treatment recommendation through collaborative filtering. The implementation emphasizes data-driven inference, enabling the discovery of latent relationships among patient records without reliance on manually defined diagnostic rules.
Code Authors
Yahya Dorostkar Navaei
Yaser Ahangari Nanehkaran
DOI: 10.1155/2022/5663001
Dataset Information
The computational workflow assumes the presence of a MATLAB dataset file named Dataset.mat, which contains the variables required for simulation. The structure of the dataset corresponds to electronic patient health records obtained from publicly available biomedical repositories. The dataset includes patient attributes, diagnostic labels, and rating-like representations used within the recommender component of the system.
The methodological foundation of the study is aligned with datasets curated in external repositories commonly used in biomedical signal processing and clinical data analysis.
Third-Party Dataset Source
PhysioNet Data Repository
https://physionet.org/
PhysioNet provides open-access physiological and clinical datasets widely adopted for reproducible research in computational medicine. Users replicating this work should ensure that the dataset organization matches the variable structure expected by the MATLAB scripts (e.g., matrices representing patient features, class labels, and record similarities).

Code Information
The MATLAB implementation encapsulates the following functional components:
•	Loading and preprocessing of patient records
•	Similarity computation using Euclidean distance measures
•	Neighborhood discovery for instance-based reasoning
•	Mean-centered normalization of record values
•	Collaborative filtering for prediction and recommendation
•	Error estimation using Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
•	Classification via multiple machine learning algorithms
•	Performance evaluation and visualization
Custom MATLAB functions required for execution:
•	KNN – K-Nearest Neighbor classifier
•	DT – Decision Tree classifier
•	NB – Naïve Bayes classifier
•	NN – Neural Network classifier
•	Confusion – Confusion matrix computation
These functions must be available within the MATLAB path prior to execution.

Usage Instructions
1.	Place the dataset file (Dataset.mat) in the MATLAB working directory.
2.	Ensure that all dependent function files (KNN.m, DT.m, NB.m, NN.m, Confusion.m) are accessible.
3.	Execute the main MATLAB script:
clc;
clear;
close all;
load Dataset;
4.	Run the script sequentially. The program performs similarity analysis, prediction, classification, and graphical evaluation automatically.

